        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="http://geosound.ddns.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            View Deployed Version (Note: Live status depends on project usage)
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="project-card" aria-labelledby="project-motamayezoon">
      <h2 id="project-motamayezoon">Motamayezoon Library API</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Technologies:</strong> Node.js, Express, MongoDB, Mongoose,
        RESTful APIs.
      </p>
      <p>
        A robust backend API designed to support the Motamayezoon team in their
        mission to convert accessible reading materials for blind and visually
        impaired users. The API manages book uploads, categorizes resources, and
        links them with book series. It supports three formats:
        <strong>KFX, EPUB, and AZW3</strong>, allowing users to easily download
        clean, well-formatted materials tailored for screen readers.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/bassem-krayem/motamyezon_for_text_books_v2"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
          >
            Source Code on GitHub
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="project-card" aria-labelledby="project-portfolio">
